The "Win-Win Cooperation: Belt and Road International Printmaking Exchange Project Achievement Exhibition" was unveiled at the Palace Museum Saturday. Artists along the Belt and Road, with their hands and wisdom, present the culture of their own countries via printmaking to visitors, enabling more people to share the spirit and value of art, said Wang Xudong, the new curator of the Palace Museum. Six teams of teachers and students, as well as 10 families, were invited to the opening ceremony, during which the children were instructed to complete printmaking works with characteristic of the Palace Museum. May 18 marks International Museum Day. This exhibition is among a series of events the Palace Museum hosted for visitors. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starUnrealistic expectations thwart Chinese job recruitersDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los Angeles